00:08:50.350 --> 00:08:53.080
&gt;&gt; Rachel Renee Russell:
Good morning everyone.

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:56.980
I'm excited to be here.

00:08:56.980 --> 00:09:02.330
I just wanted to say a few
words, and I wanted to talk

00:09:02.330 --> 00:09:09.000
about why we need diverse
books in 2017.

00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:12.480
Many individuals are passionate
about increasing diversity

00:09:12.480 --> 00:09:17.860
in children's literature and
those numbers are growing daily.

00:09:17.860 --> 00:09:23.870
On March 15th, 2014, the late
celebrated author Walter D. Myers

00:09:23.870 --> 00:09:27.520
and his son Christopher Myers,
both wrote out their pieces

00:09:27.520 --> 00:09:31.320
for the New York Times
about the lack of diversity

00:09:31.320 --> 00:09:37.180 position:56%
in children's literature mere months
before the hashtag We Need Diverse

00:09:37.180 --> 00:09:39.460
Books was created.

00:09:39.460 --> 00:09:43.380
The editorial piece was
titled "Where are the People

00:09:43.380 --> 00:09:46.640
of Color in Children's Books?"

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:52.120
It helped spark and renewed
the debate and passion

00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:56.570
for change that we're seeing today.

00:09:56.570 --> 00:09:59.880
Was it [inaudible] who read that
article in the New York Times

00:09:59.880 --> 00:10:01.180
and decided to take action?

00:10:01.180 --> 00:10:11.620
No. It was mostly young adults,
book bloggers, authors, librarians.

00:10:12.670 --> 00:10:14.240
And others.

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:17.480
Many of you here today.

00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:21.150
It made me want to change things.

00:10:21.150 --> 00:10:24.040
Since then, We Need
Diverse Books has grown

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:29.520
from a simple hashtag
to a powerful movement.

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:32.240
One that is increasing the
number of diverse books

00:10:32.240 --> 00:10:36.280
and diverse authors
published in our society.

00:10:36.280 --> 00:10:39.210
We must continue to
advocate for change

00:10:39.210 --> 00:10:43.610
because the situation is
more urgent than ever.

00:10:43.610 --> 00:10:48.950
Recent data from the US Census
Bureau indicates that almost half

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:51.110
of the American children
born under the age

00:10:51.110 --> 00:10:55.590
of five years old are
people of color.

00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:58.520
We need to make a concerted
effort to ensure that the books

00:10:58.520 --> 00:11:04.420 position:56%
that they will be reading are a
reflection of the world around them.

00:11:04.420 --> 00:11:08.850
These books must contain
characters as diverse

00:11:08.850 --> 00:11:13.070
as the children reading them.

00:11:13.070 --> 00:11:18.330
So, how can we make
change for the better?

00:11:18.330 --> 00:11:22.800
There's no easy answer, but I
think the logical first step is

00:11:22.800 --> 00:11:24.740
to continue to increase the number

00:11:24.740 --> 00:11:28.130
of diverse children's
authors being published.

00:11:28.130 --> 00:11:30.930
The end result will be
an increase in the number

00:11:30.930 --> 00:11:33.500
of books for diversive children.

00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:37.680
I personally know there are authors
out there, manuscripts in hand,

00:11:37.680 --> 00:11:41.240
waiting patiently to help
change the landscape.

00:11:41.240 --> 00:11:44.630
So who will also benefit from
diverse books in addition

00:11:44.630 --> 00:11:47.140
to the children from
diverse backgrounds?

00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:51.500
Everyone. In an assembly
of people from all facets

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:54.730
of the publishing industry,
publishing houses, booksellers,

00:11:54.730 --> 00:11:57.810
book bloggers, authors,
librarians, et cetera,

00:11:57.810 --> 00:12:01.580
as well as the general
public including adults,

00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:03.600
teens, and children.

00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:08.300
I think everyone will better
relate to books when the authors

00:12:08.300 --> 00:12:13.890
and characters reflect them
and or our society at large.

00:12:13.890 --> 00:12:18.260
This annual award ceremony
is the perfect time and place

00:12:18.260 --> 00:12:20.110
to continue this conversation

00:12:20.110 --> 00:12:24.250
and recommit ourselves
to making these changes.

00:12:24.250 --> 00:12:27.370
Although I have diverse
characters in my Dork Diary books,

00:12:27.370 --> 00:12:30.760
I felt compelled to do even better.

00:12:30.760 --> 00:12:32.540
To do more.

00:12:32.540 --> 00:12:37.850
To say more because our
children deserve it.

00:12:37.850 --> 00:12:40.760
This is both a challenging
and exciting time

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:48.510
for the publishing industry, and I
am confident that we will succeed.

