Walter flame had ignited in me.

00:25:28.790 --> 00:25:31.690
I caught a bit of his musing.

00:25:31.690 --> 00:25:35.520
So for me to stand here in the
Library of Congress at a moment

00:25:35.520 --> 00:25:37.570
when I believe we are living

00:25:37.570 --> 00:25:41.420
under an administration
that is anti-knowledge.

00:25:41.420 --> 00:25:45.570
It aims to snuff out
that twinkle in our eyes.

00:25:45.570 --> 00:25:51.080
That hunger to tell stories that
have not been seen or heard.

00:25:51.080 --> 00:25:56.230
We live in a moment of blockade,
of restriction, of walling off.

00:25:56.230 --> 00:26:00.100
Banning, suppressing the
glorious and intemperate river

00:26:00.100 --> 00:26:02.590
that is human experience.

00:26:02.590 --> 00:26:04.420
A book is the opposite.

00:26:04.420 --> 00:26:06.530
A novel is the opposite.

00:26:06.530 --> 00:26:08.170
There are no walls.

00:26:08.170 --> 00:26:09.530
Not in our readers.

00:26:09.530 --> 00:26:10.970
Not as authors.

00:26:10.970 --> 00:26:13.630
There's only the ceaseless
exploration

00:26:13.630 --> 00:26:17.210
of the human experience
in all its diversity.

00:26:17.210 --> 00:26:19.230
So I came to write "Watched."

00:26:19.230 --> 00:26:23.250
A young Muslim boy's morale
odyssey as he navigates the shoals

00:26:23.250 --> 00:26:29.500
of a world saturated and watching,
surveillance, profiling, suspicion.

00:26:29.500 --> 00:26:33.980
His very identity is
trapped, walled in, confined.

00:26:33.980 --> 00:26:37.050
He's a Bangladeshi
teenager like any teenager.

00:26:37.050 --> 00:26:42.750
Mixed up, a screw up, a boy with
a serious case of senioritis.

00:26:42.750 --> 00:26:48.200
And yet for him as a young Muslim,
the cost of any misstep is higher.

00:26:48.200 --> 00:26:50.430
Somehow, he must find his manhood.

00:26:50.430 --> 00:26:54.100
He must find his sense of
agency and morale truth.

00:26:54.100 --> 00:26:58.670
